      "writtenOn": "2017-05-22T12:16:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u0027typographic point\u0027\nIn css \u0027pt\u0027 is a thing -- is it really a thing in Skia? It\u0027s not a word -- spelling it as an abbreviation looks weird\n\u00271 pt. equals 1/72 of an inch\u0027...\n\nFurther, most style guides would use \u0027One\u0027 in place of \u00271\u0027 here. I would probably write this as\n\nPDF_Page uses Typographic_Point to describe text and geometry size. One point equals 1/72 of an inch, which is approximately 127/360 millimeters. \n\nI can\u0027t find any online reference to a point defined in terms of mm though. Is this an Adobe-ism?",
      "range": {
